    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "54bc0d0da96fd63c",
      "text": "This starts a ssh tunnel session where a connection to port 9221 on your local machine will be forwarded to port 9229 on remote.example.com. You can now attach a debugger such as [[Chrome DevTools]] or [[Visual Studio Code]] to localhost:9221, which should be able to debug as if the Node.js application was running locally."
